The course is comprised of lectures and seminars in which the fundamental framework, most important methods as well as questions central to the methodology of the study of culture and religion are discussed.  Additionally the students are expected to complete three small home assignments and one larger assignment.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To present an overview of the fundamental framework, most important methods and questions central to the methodology of the study of culture and religion.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the completion of the course the student: - is basic knowledge about the fundamental methodological framework in the study of culture and religion - has acquired elementary skills in the application and the main research methods - comprehends central methodological issues and questions in the study of culture and religion - is capable of arguing in favour of his/her position in a clear and critical manner.
